title: Right Now
body: [Intro] D D A A It's time to let it go. You say you understand. G G D D Some truth is never known until you've lost your hand. D D A A Until you've had to fight and waited through the night. G G D D* You won't know if it's real until you have to deal. [Chorus] G A Why'd you have to go and make it weird D G saying things you think I need to hear. G A I don't need to know what makes it last, D G you can slow down, I ain't going fast. E G* All those days are done. [Verse 2] D D A A We all know that it's hard, hard to stay forever G G D D but I'm telling you right now if we're apart or here together. D D A A I need to be myself, I won't live another lie G G D D* about the feelings that I have, I won't be with you and hide. [End-Chorus] G A Why'd you have to go and make it weird D G saying things you think I need to hear. G A I don't need to know what makes it last, D G you can slow down, I ain't going fast. E G All those days are done. E G All those times are gone. I'm telling you E All those times are gone. [Outro] G E I'm telling you right now, right now. G E I'm telling you right now, right now. G E I'm telling you right now, right now. G E I need you to look at me and listen. G E G I ain't the past coming back to haunt you. E G I'm telling you right now, right now. E G I'm telling you right now, right now. E G I'm telling you right now, right now. E G I'm telling you right now, right now. E G I'm telling you right now, right now. E* I'm telling you right now, right now.

title: Ive Lied
body: G C Sitting here in this lonely old guest house G D G G7 I’m sure that my life is all through G C Scratching fleas and watching a grey mouse G D G G7 I’m making love to the memory of you G C For without you I’m weak and uncertain G D G G7 And I feel so naked and cold G C Like a window without any curtains G D G G7 My innermost feelings unfold C The drink I just had G G7 It wasn’t as bad as the first C And drinking won’t do G D When it’s only for you I thirst, I thirst G C For your kiss it quenches all burning G D G G7 And it’s sweeter than the sweetest of wine G C Now you’re gone I find myself yearning G D G G7 For the love that I left behind C Nobody can heal G G7 The pain that I feel inside C And if I said I’m strong G D G And I’m never wrong – I lied, I lied... I lied

title: Big Bad Bushranger
body: [Verse 1] D A Oh, out in the bush where the kookaburras fly where the gum trees reach to the clear blue sky D A D There's a cave in the hillside where I hide, I'm a big, bad bush-bushranger D A Deep in the cave there's a big, black hole that's filled to the brim with locks of gold D A D And diamond rings and things I stole, I'm a big, bad bush-bush ranger [Pre-Chorus 1] G D A D Late at night when the sun goes down and everyone's asleep in town G D A D I count all my money in my dressing gown, I'm a big, bad bush-bushranger [Chorus] D I'm a bush, I'm a bush, I'm a bush-bush ranger A Runnin' from the law, livin' on danger D Bang, bang, hands up, stick 'em up straight A D I'm a big, bad bush-bush ranger [Verse 2] D A Got a rope and a whip and a gun, of course, I'm chased everywhere by the bush police-force D A D While I ride through the night on my big black horse, I'm a big, bad, bush-bush ranger D A And when the townsfolk see me ride they lock all the doors and stay inside D A D And find a place that's safe to hide, I'm a big, bad, bush-bush ranger [Pre-Chorus 2] G D A D I ride thirty miles through the wind and hail to hold up a bank or the Royal Mail G D A D I give all my money to my girlfriend, Gayle, I'm a big, bad, bush-bush ranger [Chorus] D I'm a bush, I'm a bush, I'm a bush-bush ranger A Runnin' from the law, livin' on danger D Bang, bang, hands up, stick 'em up straight A D I'm a big, bad bush-bushranger [Verse 3] D A I sleep every mornin' till half past nine, have m'brekky in bed, then rise and shine D A Get dressed in my best for my life of crime, A D I'm a big, bad bush-bushranger G D A I'm loved by the married woman everywhere, while their silly old husbands curse and swear D A I haven't got a worry and I haven't got a care A D I'm a big, bad bush-bushranger G A I'm a terror of North-West New South Wales, of small bush towns and outback trails D A I don't like judges and I don't like gaols A D I'm a big, bad bush-bushranger [Chorus] D I'm
